==Graphics and Animation==

Each monster uses 1-4 tiles from the CHR ROM for its sprite representation. Monster graphics are stored in CHR Bank 0 starting at $0400.

Monster animation frames:
* Most monsters: 2 frames (idle/attack)
* Dragons: 4 frames (idle/rear/attack/breath)
* Slimes: 1 frame (static)
* Dragonlord: 8 frames (transformation sequence)

==Technical Notes==

* Monster data is stored in Bank 1 at $9000-$94FF
* Each monster entry is exactly 16 bytes
* HP values are ranges - exact HP is randomly determined within range
* Metal Slime and Goldman have special AI routines for fleeing
* Dragon breath attacks ignore armor defense
* Undead monsters take extra damage from certain spells

